en: A medium range optically guided "fire-and-forget" anti-tank missile.
ko: 발사후 망각 기능이 탑재된 광학 유도식 중거리 대-전차 미사일입니다.

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the basic weapons tutorial.
Today, we will be covering weapon configuration, target acquisition, and firing weapons.
ko: 오늘은,  무기 설정법, 표적 설정법 그리고 무기를 발사 하는 방법을 배울것입니다.

en: Let's start by setting the MFDs to the pages we will use.
ko: 이제, MFD를 우리가 사용할 페이지로 설정해 봅시다.

en: The EQUIP page shows what you have on each of the vehicle's equipment mounts.
ko: EQUIP 페이지는 기체가 장비하고 있는 무기들을 보여줍니다.

en: It displays information on each item, and allows you to arm/disarm, configure, or mark them for jettison.
ko: 이 페이지에서 각 무기들을 무장하거나 해제 시킬 수 있으며, 설정하거나 투하할 목록 으로 표시 할 수도 있습니다.

en: We'll go over each feature in more detail later.
ko: 각 기능에 대한 구체적인 사항은 조금 뒤에 살펴보겠습니다.

en: The TGP is what you will use to acquire ground targets.
ko: TGP로 지상 목표물들의 표적을 지시할 것입니다.

en: To use it, first you must supply power to the sensor mounted under the nose of the vehicle.
ko: 사용하기 위해서는 먼저, 기체의 아래에 장착되어 있는 센서로 전원을 공급해야 합니다.

en: The TGP will be in FWD mode by default, which just looks straight forward.
ko: TGP는 기본으로 FWD 모드로 설정되어 있을 것입니다. 전방 모드에서는 기본값으로 앞을 바라보고 있습니다.

en: To be able to control it, you must designate the TGP as the sensor of interest (SOI).
ko: 표적지시기를 조정하기 위해서는, TGP를 SOI(활성 센서)로 설 정해야 합니다.

en: Now, you can slew the targeting sensor around using the thumb control on your joystick.
ko: 이제, 조이스틱의 엄지 컨트롤로 표적지시기의 시야 방향을 조정할 수 있습니다.

en: Try slewing the TGP around using the joystick thumb control.
ko: TGP의 시야를 조이스틱의 엄지 컨트롤러로 조작해 보십시오.

en: When you move the sensor, it will auto switch to TGT mode, which locks its focus point on the ground while you're flying.
ko: 센서를 움직이면, 자동적으로 TGT모드로 전환할 것입니다. 타겟 모드는 비행중에 지상의 한 점에 시야를 고정 시킵니다.

en: The yellow arrow on the screen shows the relative bearing to the target point.
ko: 화면상의 노란 화살표는 표적과의 상대적인 베어링을 보여줍니다.

en: The target point also shows up on the NAV map as a yellow cross.
ko: 또한 표적 지점은 NAV 지도상에서 노란 십자가로 표시 됩니다.

en: Now let's find some targets.  Take off and fly to the objective waypoint.
ko: 이제 표적들을 한번 찾아 봅시다. 이륙한뒤 목표 경유지로 이동하십시오.

en: Now that we are in the AO, you can enable the Master Arm switch.
ko: 이제 작전지역에 진입했으니, Master Arms 스위치를 활성화 하십시오.

en: With the weapon system armed, you will see some new icons on the HUD
ko: 무기 시스템이 활성화 된 뒤, 몇 가지의 새로운 아이콘이 HUD 상에 나타날 것 입니다.

en: At the center, you have the weapon targeting reticle or pipper.
Here, you have weapon type, name, and shots remaining.
ko: 여기에는 무기의 종류, 이름, 그리고 남은 장탄수가 나타납니다.

en: You can cycle through all ARMED weapons by pressing the button on the joystick.
ko: 무장된 무기들을 조이스틱의 버튼을 누르면서 바꿀 수 있습니다.

en: These unguided weapons can be fired by simply pulling the trigger on the joystick.
ko: 이런 비유도 무기들을 발사하기 위해서는, 단순히 조이스틱의 트리거를 누르면 됩니다.

en: You have limited stores so save your rounds for the targets.
ko: 장탄수가 제한되어 있으니 표적들을 위해 아껴놓으십시오.

en: Let's try deploying the GAU-8 on some ground targets.
ko: 이제 GAU-8을 지상 목표물들에 사용해 봅시다.

en: In a moment, you'll receive a mission objective.
ko: 잠시후 임무 목표를 받게 될 것입니다.

en: You can auto-slew your TGP to the objective waypoint by pressing the WPT button in the TGP screen.
ko: TGP를 자동으로 목표 지점을 보게 하려면, TGP 스크린 상에서 WPT 버튼을 누르면 됩니다.

en: Go ahead and destroy the tanks.
Great job!  Now let's work with rockets.
By default, each pull of the trigger will fire one rocket.
ko: 기본 설정값으로는, 트리거를 한번 누를시 한발만 나가도록 설정되어 있습니다.

en: However, they can be configured to launch rapidly.  This is called 'ripple' firing.
ko: 반면, 속사 기능을 사용하도록 설정할 수도 있습니다.

en: To access a weapons config menu, set the EQUIP MFD page to CONFIG mode
ko: 무기의 설정 메뉴로 진입 하려면, EQUIP MFP 페이지에 서 CONFIG 모드로 진입 하십시오.

en: Then, select the weapon you want to configure.
If you have multiple of the same weapon, the settings will be copied over to all of them.
ko: 같은 무기를 다수를 지니고 있을 경우 자동으로 설정이 모두에게 복사 될 것입니다.

en: Try setting the rockets to different ripple intervals and destroy the next set of targets.
ko: 로켓을 다양한 속사 속도로 설정한 뒤, 다음 주어진 표적들을 파괴하십시오.

en: Well done! You've destroyed all of the targets.
This concludes the basic weapons tutorial.
ko: 이것으로 기본 무기 튜토리얼을 마치도록 하겠습니다.

Description: Full equip name of: EUCAV GUN
Full equip name of: GBU-53 Advanced SD Bomb x4
Item description of: GBU-53 Advanced SD Bomb x4
en: An internally mounted rack of 4 optically guided small diameter bomb. Each bomb has built-in folding wings that allow it to glide for long distances and hit targets with precision. Advanced optics allow it to track moving targets from extended range without laser designation.
ko: 내부 무장창에 탑재된 4발의 광학 유도식 소구경 폭탄입니다. 각 폭탄은 부착된 접이식 날개로 장거리 활강과 정밀 유도가 가능합니다. 향상된 광학인식 장비는 이동식 목표물을 장거리에서 레이저 유도 없이 추적 가능하게 해줍니다.

Description: Full equip name of: AGM-145 Ballista x4
Item description of: AGM-145 Ballista x4
en: Small anti-tank missiles with advanced optics, "fire and forget", and smart self-targeting technology. Can be fired without line of sight to the designated target point, and will acquire hostile targets automatically.
ko: 고급 광학 장치, "발사 후 망각"및 개선된 자가 표적 식별 기술을 탑재한 소형 대전차 미사일. 시야각 외의 지정된 목표 지점까지 발사 할 수 있으며 적대적 표적들을 자동으로 추적합니다.

Description: Full equip name of: SB-1 x32

en: A rack of 32 standard un-guided 500lb bombs.

Description: Full equip name of: AGM-126 SideARM II x1
Item description of: AGM-126 SideARM II x1
en: Compact short range anti-radiation missile based on the AIM-9x.
ko: AIM-9x를 소형화 한 단거리 대-레이더 미사일 입니다.

Description: Full equip name of: AGM-65 x3

en: A medium range optically guided "fire-and-forget" anti-tank missile.
ko: 발사후 망각 기능이 탑재된 광학 유도식 중거리 대-전차 미사일입니다.

Full equip name of: CAGM-6 Cluster Missile
Item description of: CAGM-6 Cluster Missile
en:
An optically guided "fire-and-forget" missile. 
Deploys 6 submunitions that independently seek targets in the field of view.
ko:
광학유도식 "발사 후 망각" 기능이 탑재된 미사일.
전개 후 시야각에 있는 최대 6개의 개별 목표물에 집속탄을 발사합니다.

Description: Full equip name of: MAD-4 Missile

en: Standard radar-guided missile built for the Mobile Air Defense launcher. It has a range of about 55km (30nm).
ko: 지상 이동식 대공망을 위해 설계된 재래식 레이더 유도 대공 미사일. 약 55키로(30nm)의 사거리를 가지고 있습니다.

en: Dual stage long range radar-guided missile that deploys a field of explosive munitions.
ko: 이단 부스터가 장착된 장거리 레이더 유도 미사일, 목표물에 집속탄을 뿌립니다.

Description: Full equip name of: 4200L Fuel Drop Tank
Item description of: 4200L Fuel Drop Tank
Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: First, let's keep the bird from rolling away.
Now lets move on to the start-up sequence.
Let the APU spool up a bit.
Wait for the engines to spool up.
ko: 엔진 RPM이 안정화 될때 까지 기다립니다.

en: The engines are now supplying power.  We can turn off the APU.
ko: 엔진이 이제 전원을 공급하니 APU를 꺼도 됩니다.

en: The HUD (Heads-Up Display) shows you attitude, altitude, velocity, targeting reticles, and other important flight data at a glance.
ko: HUD (헤드-업-디스플레이)는 고도, 방위, 속도, 목표물 등 과 같은 중요한 비행정도를 즉각적으로 볼 수 있게 표시해 줍니다.

en: The MFDs (Multi-Function Displays) give you access to
aircraft features such as weapon configuration, navigation maps,
sensors, etc.  You can access these features by pressing the corresponding buttons around the edge of the monitor.
ko: 센서 등과 같은 기체 설정을 하도록 돕습니다. 이러한 설정은 모니터 주변의 각 버튼을 눌러서 접근할 수 있습니다.

en: The vehicle is now ready to fly.  Up next: Basic Flight
ko: 이제 기체가 이륙 준비가 되었습니다. 다음 기본 비행으로 넘어갑시다.

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the Basic Flight tutorial.
We'll skip the start-up procedure now.
The main flight controls are the joystick and throttle.  You can grip them by holding the grip buttons, or toggle lock your hands to them by tapping the grip buttons.
ko: 주된 비행 조작법은 조이스틱과 스로틀 입니다. 그립 버튼으로 잡을 수 있습니다. 혹은 그립 버튼을 한번 누름으로 잡기를 토글 할 수도 있습니다.

en: To steer the front wheel, you will have to twist the joystick on the vertical axis.
ko: 앞 바퀴를 조종하려면, 조이스틱을 수직을 축으로 해서 비트십시오.

en: In order to get moving, we need to tilt the engines to the forward position.
ko: 움직이기 위해서는 엔진을 앞을 보도록 각도를 변경해야 합니다.

en: Hold the throttle trigger to lock the brakes
ko: 브레이크를 잠그기 위해서 스로틀 트리거를 누르고 있으십시오.

en: Then press and hold up on the throttle thumb control to tilt the engines forward.
ko: 그 다음 스로틀 엄지 스틱을 위로 한뒤 눌러 엔진의 각도를 앞으로 기울이십시오.

en: If you release the brakes and slightly lift the throttle lever, you will start to roll.
ko: 브레이크 잠금을 풀고 스로틀 레버를 살짝 올리면 굴러가기 시작할 것입니다.

en: Apply small amounts of throttle or brakes to control your speed.
ko: 속도를 조절하기 위해 브레이크와 스로틀을 사용하며 이동하십시오.

en: Full stop!  Throttle down and hold the throttle brake trigger.
ko: 정지! 스로틀을 내리고 브레이크 트리거를 잡으십시오.

en: Let's prepare for a conventional take-off.
Set the brake lock so you can free up your hands.
ko: 손을 자유롭게 하기 위해 브레이크 잠금을 활성화 하십시오.

en: Make sure all flight assists are enabled
ko: 비행 보조가 활성화 되어 있는지 확인 하십시오.

en: Check that the engines are tilted all the way forward.
ko: 엔진이 완전히 전면을 향하고 있는지 확인하십시오.

en: Now grab the throttle and hold the brakes...
Now.. to take off, raise the throttle to full and steer to keep aligned with the runway.
ko: 이륙을 위해서는 스로틀을 최대로 올리고 활주로와 정렬되도록 조종하면 됩니다.

en: Speed up to [80]! Straight down the runway!
Now carefully rotate the joystick back to pull the nose up!
ko: 이제 조심스럽게 조이스틱을 뒤로 당기며 기수를 올리십시오.

en: Now gently steer your nose to about 20 degrees and keep climbing to {1000} ASL.
ko: 이제 부드럽게 기수를 20도 정도 올리며 {1000} ASL 까지 상승하십시오.
이제, 기본적인 비행 제어를 연습 해 봅시다.

en: Rotate the joystick left or right to roll towards your target
ko: 조이스틱을 좌우로 움직여 기체의 롤(roll)을 조종하십시오.

en: Rotate the joystick forward or back to pitch your nose towards it.
ko: 조이스틱을 앞뒤로 움직여 기체의 피치(pitch)를 조종하십시오.

en: This is your velocity vector, showing the direction you are moving.
ko: 이것이 속도 벡터입니다. 이것이 현재 움직임의 방향을 보여줍니다.

en: You want to steer velocity vector towards where you want to go.
ko: 가고자 하는 곳으로 속도 백터를 이동시키며 비행하십시오.

en: Great flying! Now let's try to land at the airbase.
ko: 멋진 비행솜씨입니다! 이제 공항에 착륙해 봅시다.

en: Start your landing here at about [150]
Line up with the runway and bring speed down to about [100]
ko: 활주로와 정렬한 뒤 속도를 약 [100] 정도로 감소시키십시오.

en: Flaps down, gear down.  Speed down to [80]
ko: 플랩 내리고, 바퀴 내리고, 속도 [80]까지 감속.

en: Maintain speed and glide slope.  Keep the vector on target!
ko: 속도와 하강을 유지하십시오. 속도 벡터를 목표 활주로에 유지하십시오!

en: Prepare to flare nose up for a smooth landing
ko: 부드러운 착륙을 위해 기수를 높일 준비를 하십시오.

en: Touch down! Bring your nose down.
Steer down the runway, throttle down and carefully apply brakes.
ko: 활주로를 타며, 스토틀을 내리고 천천히 브레이크를 거십시오.

en: Congratulations!  This concludes the basic flight tutorial.
ko: 축하합니다! 이로서 기본 비행 튜토리얼을 마치도록 하겠습니다.

Description: Full equip name of: AIM-120D Advanced Radar Missile x2
Item description of: AIM-120D Advanced Radar Missile x2
en: Two internally mounted, radar guided, medium range air to air missiles.
ko: 내부 무장창에 탑재된, 2발의 레이더 유도 중거리 공대공 미사일 입니다.

Description: Full equip name of: AGM-145 Ballista x2
Item description of: AGM-145 Ballista x2
en: Small anti-tank missiles with advanced optics, "fire and forget", and smart self-targeting technology. Can be fired without line of sight to the designated target point, and will acquire hostile targets automatically.
ko: 고급 광학 장치, "발사 후 망각"및 개선된 자가 표적 식별 기술을 탑재한 소형 대전차 미사일. 시야각 외의 지정된 목표 지점까지 발사 할 수 있으며 적대적 표적들을 자동으로 추적합니다.

Description: Full equip name of: Mk-82 Bomb x1
Item description of: Mk-82 Bomb x1
Full equip name of: AIM-120 Advanced Radar Missile x2
Item description of: AIM-120 Advanced Radar Missile x2
en: A rack of two radar guided medium range air to air missiles.
ko: 2발의 레이더 유도 중거리 공대공 미사일 입니다.

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the Vertical Flight autopilot training.
Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the AP, you will be a master in no time.
ko: 수직 비행은 고난이도 기술이지만, 오토파일럿(AP) 기능을 통해 빠른 시간 안에 숙달이 가능합니다.

en: First, make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.
ko: 먼저, 엔진이 90 각도로 틀어져 있는지 확인 하십시오.

en: First, make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.
ko: 먼저, 엔진이 90 각도로 틀어져 있는지 확인 하십시오.

en: The HVR mode will assist you in staying upright and keeping your horizontal velocity under control.
ko: HVR 모드는 뒤집히지 않도록 보조해주며 수직 속도를 조정해 줍니다.

en: The ALT mode will take control of the engines and convert inputs into climb or descent rates.
ko: ALT 모드는 엔진조정을 담당하며 입력을 상승 혹은 하강 속도로 치환시켜 줍니다.

en: Keeping your throttle centered will hold a hover
Raise or lower the throttle to climb or descend
ko: 스로틀을 올리거나 내려서 상승 혹은 하강하십시

en: Keep your left thumb away from the tilt control.
Any engine tilt less than 90 will disengage HVR AP
ko: 90도 이하의 엔진 각도는 자동으로 HVR과 Ap를 비활성화 시킵니다.

en: Lift throttle now.  Climb to {50} altitude.
Now set your throttle lever to the midpoint to hover.
ko: 이제 스로틀을 중앙으로 위치시켜 호버링 하십시오.

en: You should now be in a stable hover
You can make adjustments to the throttle to climb or descend as needed.
ko: 스로틀을 조정해 상승 혹은 하강이 가능합니다.

en: Now you can use the joystick to move around
The HVR autopilot will handle attitude control
ko: HVR 오토 파일럿이 고도 조정을 자동으로 담당할 것입니

en: You just have to tilt the joystick in the direction you want to go
ko: 조이스틱을 움직이기만 하면, 자동으로 가고자 하는 곳으로 이동이 가능합니다.

en: You can also twist the joystick to yaw
As you move around, study how the AP handles the vehicle
ko: 움직임에 따라 AP가 어떻게 기체를 조정하는지 연구해 보십시오

en: Let's try flying into some targets.
Great! Now lets try to land back on the helipad.
ko: 멋집니다! 이제 다시 헬리패드에 착륙해 봅시다.

en: Bring yourself to a stop by centering the throttle, and steering the stick in the opposite direction as your horizontal velocity indicator.
ko: 스로틀을 중앙에 정렬시켜 정지한뒤 수직 속도 표시기와 반대 방향으로 스틱을 조정하십시오.

en: Rotate to face towards the helipads.
Begin to move towards the pad.  Adjust your altitude control and steer so your velocity vector is pointed just above the pad.
ko: 헬리패드를 향해 움직이십시오. 고도조정과 스티어링을 조정하며 속도 벡터가 패드 바로 위에 있도록 조정하십시오.

en: Slow your forward speed and rate of descent.
Adjust rate of descent to bring it down gently.
Touch down!  Throttle down and enable brake locks.
ko: 터치다운! 스로틀을 내리고 브레이크 록을 거십시오.

en: Congratulations!  Next time: Manual vertical flight and transitioning.
ko: 축하합니다! 다음 튜토리얼: 수동 수직 이착륙과 변환

Description: Short description of playable vehicle AV-42C
en: "Kestrel" Multi-role VTOL aircraft. Tilting jet nozzles give it the ability to take off and land vertically or horizontally. Large cargo bay and multiple weapon mounts allow for both transport and attack missions.
ko: "Kestrel" 다목적 수직 이착륙 항공기. 틸팅 엔진 노즐을 사용하면 수직으로 이착륙하거나 수평으로 날 수 있습니다. 대형 화물칸과 여러 개의 무기 랙으로 운송과 공격 임무를 동시에 수행 할 수 있습니다.

Description: Short description of playable vehicle F/A-26B
en: "Wasp" Carrier based air-superiority fighter that can also be configured for ground attack roles.
ko: "Wasp" 함재기 전투기는 대공은 물론 지상 공격 임무로 무장을 구성 할 수도 있습니다.

Description: Short description of playable vehicle F-45A
en: "Ghost" Stealthy, single-engine, VTOL/STOVL capable aircraft with four internal bays. Optional external hardpoints can be used to increase carrying capacity when stealth is not needed.
ko: "Ghost" 스텔스 단일 엔진 수직 / 단거리 이착륙 전투기, 4 개의 내장 무기 베이를 지녔으며, 스텔스가 필요하지 않은 경우 외부 파일론을 사용하여 무기 무장 능력을 높일 수 있습니다.

en: Help make preparations to defend the island. Transport personnel to coastal SAM site.
ko: 섬을 방어하는 과정을 도우십시오. 병력을 해안가의 지대공 사이트로 수송 하십시오.

en: Let the soldiers into your passenger bay.
Drop the soldiers off at the east bay SAM site.
ko: 병사들을 SAM 사이트 동쪽에 있는 해안만에 내려주십시오.

en: Join up with the fighter escort wing.
Pick up the survivors from the crash site.
Deliver the survivors to the hospital.
Return to and land at the airbase.
Allow the fighters to clear out the hostile drones.
Destroy the drone ships laying mines on supply routes.
ko: 보급로에 수중 지뢰를 살포하는 드론 선박을 파괴 하십시오.

en: Meet up with Victor1 at the waypoint.
Lead the strike group to the area of operations.
If able, support your wingmen by destroying the carrier's weapons and drones.
ko: 가능하다면 항공 모함의 무기와 드론을 파괴하여 윙맨을 지원하세요.

en: Join the carrier fleet embarking on a pre-emptive naval strike.
ko: 선제 공격을 시작하는 항공 모함 편대에 합류하십시오.

en: Search for the lost pilot near the objective waypoint.
ko: 목표 지점 근처에서 길을 잃은 조종사를 찾으십시오.

en: Lead the lost pilot to the refuel tanker.
Lead the pilot to the aircraft carrier.
Meet the enemy in open water for a pre-emptive strike.
ko: 선제 공격을 위해 공해에서 적을 만나십시오.

en: Help defend the fleet from the incoming drones.
Destroy or disable all enemy weapon systems, sensors, and drones.
ko: 모든 적의 무기 시스템, 센서 및 드론을 파괴하거나 비활성화하십시오.

en: Return to the fleet and land.
Return to the island to investigate why communications have gone silent.
Take off and fly to the aerial fuel tanker.
Allow Romeo1-2 to refuel. Then you may refuel yourself if necessary.
ko: Romeo1-2가 연료를 보급하도록합니다. 그런 다음 필요한 경우 연료를 공급할 수 있습니다.

en: Avoid the enemy fleet. Return to the waypoint and await orders.
ko: 적 함대를 피하십시오. 웨이 포인트로 돌아가 명령을 기다립니다.

en: Destroy the armored units moving toward our allied infantry.
ko: 아군 보병을 향해 이동하는 장갑 유닛을 파괴하십시오.

en: Begin a counterattack under the cover of darkness.
Take off and prepare for your anti-ship strike.
Destroy the long range missile cruiser.
Begin to take back the island and eliminate the enemy fleet off the northern coast.
ko: 섬을 되찾고 북쪽 해안에서 적 함대를 제거하십시오.

en: Destroy the incoming enemy carrier fleet.
Clear out the enemy units at the airbase.
Destroy the enemy SAM site to allow reinforcements to take off.
ko: 증원군이 이륙 할 수 있도록 적의 SAM 사이트를 파괴하십시오.

en: Rearm if necessary, then regroup with Victor 1.
Destroy the rocket-equipped drone boats threatening the carrier.
ko: 항공 모함을 위협하는 로켓이 장착 된 드론 보트를 파괴하십시오.

en: Destroy the carrier group's radars and air defenses so bombers can come to help.
ko: 폭격기가 도움을받을 수 있도록 항공 모함 그룹의 레이더와 방공 장치를 파괴하세요.

en:
Negotiations for peace have failed.  We believe the enemy will strike here first, as a stepping stone to the mainland.

We have begun preparing coastal air defenses.
ko: 평화를위한 협상은 실패했습니다. 우리는 적이 본토로가는 디딤돌로서 이곳을 먼저 공격 할 것이라고 믿습니다. 해안 방공 준비를 시작했습니다.

en:
As an AV-42C pilot, you will deliver personnel to the defense sites.

Other pilots and soldiers will be arriving by air from the mainland soon.
ko:
As an AV-42C pilot, you will deliver personnel to the defense sites.

Other pilots and soldiers will be arriving by air from the mainland soon.

en: As we continue to prepare our defenses against the invasive enemy forces, we need to secure supply routes from the mainland to the island.
ko: As we continue to prepare our defenses against the invasive enemy forces, we need to secure supply routes from the mainland to the island.

en: The troops you recovered from the crash site reported that they spotted what seemed to be unmanned vessels deploying sea mines near the south east supply route.
ko: The troops you recovered from the crash site reported that they spotted what seemed to be unmanned vessels deploying sea mines near the south east supply route.

en:
You will lead a strike group with the order of destroying all hostile targets in the designated area.  

Prepare your aircraft appropriately.
ko:
You will lead a strike group with the order of destroying all hostile targets in the designated area.  

Prepare your aircraft appropriately.

en: Our engineers were able to salvage the navigation computers from the drone ships and used them to determine the location of the main naval fleet of the enemy.
ko: Our engineers were able to salvage the navigation computers from the drone ships and used them to determine the location of the main naval fleet of the enemy.

en: We have tasked an aircraft carrier fleet to intercept before they get too close to the island.  In order to maximize their force, you and other pilots are ordered to join the fleet.
ko: We have tasked an aircraft carrier fleet to intercept before they get too close to the island.  In order to maximize their force, you and other pilots are ordered to join the fleet.

en: A pilot belonging to the carrier was out on combat air patrol when his navigation systems experienced a failure.  The pilot is lost and low on fuel, so you must quickly find him and lead him to the fuel tanker on the way to the carrier.
ko: A pilot belonging to the carrier was out on combat air patrol when his navigation systems experienced a failure.  The pilot is lost and low on fuel, so you must quickly find him and lead him to the fuel tanker on the way to the carrier.

en: We have intercepted the enemy fleet sooner than we expected to. They have already deployed aerial drones which are heading towards our fleet. All units are to scramble to defend the fleet, as well as quickly launch a counter-attack.
ko: We have intercepted the enemy fleet sooner than we expected to. They have already deployed aerial drones which are heading towards our fleet. All units are to scramble to defend the fleet, as well as quickly launch a counter-attack.

en:
The enemy force is numerous and includes small drone boats, missile cruisers, and drone carriers. This is going to get messy.

Good luck.
ko:
The enemy force is numerous and includes small drone boats, missile cruisers, and drone carriers. This is going to get messy.

Good luck.

en:
We received an encrypted message from the island airbase which suggested that a large presence was detected coming in from the north.

After that, all communications went silent.
ko:
We received an encrypted message from the island airbase which suggested that a large presence was detected coming in from the north.

After that, all communications went silent.

en:
The captain is worried that the enemy fleet we just attacked was just a diversion, and a larger enemy fleet somehow sailed to the island undetected.

We are returning to the island to investigate the radio silence.
ko:
The captain is worried that the enemy fleet we just attacked was just a diversion, and a larger enemy fleet somehow sailed to the island undetected.

We are returning to the island to investigate the radio silence.

en:
We are conserving on-board jet fuel in anticipation of responding to the potential threat, so the fighter escorts will need to refuel in the air.

Once everyone is topped off, scout the island and report back.  Good luck.
ko:
We are conserving on-board jet fuel in anticipation of responding to the potential threat, so the fighter escorts will need to refuel in the air.

Once everyone is topped off, scout the island and report back.  Good luck.

en:
On the scouting sortie, a large enemy fleet was detected north of the island.  The enemy has also begun landing ground units on the island.

Before we can begin to move in and take back the island, we need to eliminate the threat posed by the enemy long range missile cruiser.
ko:
On the scouting sortie, a large enemy fleet was detected north of the island.  The enemy has also begun landing ground units on the island.

Before we can begin to move in and take back the island, we need to eliminate the threat posed by the enemy long range missile cruiser.

en: The cruiser has an array of launch tubes which we believe are capable of deploying two-stage surface-to-air and anti-ship missiles.  It also has a vertical launching system defense cannons, so it may not be effective to use conventional bombs or air-to-ground missiles.
ko: The cruiser has an array of launch tubes which we believe are capable of deploying two-stage surface-to-air and anti-ship missiles.  It also has a vertical launching system defense cannons, so it may not be effective to use conventional bombs or air-to-ground missiles.

en: In order to take out the threat, we are authorizing the use of the AGM-89 anti-ship cruise missile.  It has advanced features such as waypoint navigation, radar target acquisition, and a large payload.  Use it wisely and destroy the high priority target.
ko: In order to take out the threat, we are authorizing the use of the AGM-89 anti-ship cruise missile.  It has advanced features such as waypoint navigation, radar target acquisition, and a large payload.  Use it wisely and destroy the high priority target.

en:
The mission launches at midnight. You will be escorted by a small wing of fighters to defend you from airborne threats.

The enemy has likely deployed more self-propelled SAM units to the island, so keep an eye out for missile launches and radar locks.

Good luck.
ko:
The mission launches at midnight. You will be escorted by a small wing of fighters to defend you from airborne threats.

The enemy has likely deployed more self-propelled SAM units to the island, so keep an eye out for missile launches and radar locks.

Good luck.

en:
With the destruction of the enemy fleet's most powerful ship, we can begin an effort to take back the island.

Through the night, the enemy has continued to deploy troops and set up defenses around the island.
ko:
With the destruction of the enemy fleet's most powerful ship, we can begin an effort to take back the island.

Through the night, the enemy has continued to deploy troops and set up defenses around the island.

en:
The first order is to clear out enemy units from the island airbase. Air defenses have been set up, so be prepared to use the surrounding hills for cover.

Once the airbase has been cleared, we can use it for refueling and rearming.
ko:
The first order is to clear out enemy units from the island airbase. Air defenses have been set up, so be prepared to use the surrounding hills for cover.

Once the airbase has been cleared, we can use it for refueling and rearming.

en:
Once that is out of the way, we must eliminate the rest of the enemy fleet parked off the norther coast.

An allied carrier fleet is arriving from the east to support us, but are unable to launch aircraft due to enemy air defenses in the eastern city.
ko:
Once that is out of the way, we must eliminate the rest of the enemy fleet parked off the norther coast.

An allied carrier fleet is arriving from the east to support us, but are unable to launch aircraft due to enemy air defenses in the eastern city.

en:
Destroy the eastern air defenses to allow the allied pilots to take off, then make a combined effort to destroy the enemy fleet.

The allied fleet will also move into firing range to support with anti-ship missiles.
ko:
Destroy the eastern air defenses to allow the allied pilots to take off, then make a combined effort to destroy the enemy fleet.

The allied fleet will also move into firing range to support with anti-ship missiles.

en: Quick flights and practice scenarios for the AV-42C.
ko: AV-42C를 위한 빠른 비행 및 연습 시나리오.

en: Free flight on a custom map.
Practice refueling in the air. Remember to lower your starting fuel.
ko: 공중에서 급유를 연습하십시오. 출격시 저장 연료를 낮추는 것을 잊지 마십시오.

en: Practice landing on the carrier or one of the cruisers.
ko: 항공 모함 또는 순양함 중 하나에 착륙하는 연습을하십시오.

en: Land on the carrier or one of the cruisers.
ko: 항공 모함 또는 순양함 중 하나에 착륙하십시오.

en: No objectives or hostiles.  Just fly around and have fun!
ko: 목표 나 적군이 없습니다. 그냥 날아 다니며 즐기세요!

en: This is a free flight, however, landing on the carrier will complete the mission
ko: 이것은 자유 비행이지만 기지에 착륙하면 임무가 완료됩니다.

en: Practice using different weapons on multiple groups of non-hostile targets.
ko: 여러 그룹의 적대적이지 않은 표적에 대해 다른 무기를 사용하는 연습을합니다.

en: Destroy the artillery on the edge of the south-eastern city.
Eliminate the enemy infantry squad patrolling near the hospital
ko: 병원 근처에서 순찰하는 적 보병 분대를 제거하십시오.

en: Destroy the armored convoy moving west from the eastern city.
ko: 동부 도시에서 서쪽으로 이동하는 장갑 호송대를 파괴하십시오.

en: Destroy the air defense network on the mountain peak.
Destroy the wing of enemy attack aircraft.
Just fly around and have fun!
A tanker is available for A2A refuelling.
ko: A2A 연료 보급을 위해 공중 급유기를 사용할 수 있습니다.

en: Try landing on one of the ships!
Practice refueling in the air. Remember to lower your starting fuel, or else the tanker won't bother lowering the boom.
ko: 공중에서 급유를 연습하십시오. 출격시 시작 연료를 낮추십시오. 그렇지 않으면 유조선이 붐을 낮추지 않습니다.

en:
Practice landing on the ships.  For the carrier, you can land vertically or with the arrestor cables.

The carrier will be moving from east to west.  Use the NAV screen on the MFD to aid you in your approach.
ko: 배에 착륙하는 연습을하십시오. 항모의 경우 수직으로 또는 어레스팅 케이블을 사용하여 착륙 할 수 있습니다. 항모는 동쪽에서 서쪽으로 이동할 것입니다. MFD의 NAV 화면을 사용하면 접근하는데 도움이 됩니다.

en:
There are no objectives. Just fly around and have fun!

There is an aircraft carrier at sea and an aerial refueling tanker in the sky.
ko: 임무가 없습니다. 그냥 날아 다니며 즐기세요! 바다에는 항공 모함이 있고 하늘에는 공중 급유 유조선이 있습니다.

en:
There are multiple groups of surface and air targets for you to practice on.

Check the waypoints and information in the Objectives MFD page.
ko: 연습 할 수 있는 여러 그룹의 지상 및 공중 표적이 있습니다. 목표 MFD 페이지에서 웨이 포인트와 정보를 확인하세요.

en: Several ground and air targets to practice deploying your weapons on. Targets will not shoot back.
ko: 무기 배치를 연습 할 여러 지상 및 공중 표적. 표적은 반격하지 않습니다.

en: Destroy the column of vehicles crossing the bridge.
Destroy the bomber and its escorts flying at high altitude.
ko: 높은 고도에서 비행하는 폭격기와 호위병을 파괴하십시오.

en: Destroy the radar network around the central mountains.
ko: 중앙 산 주변의 레이더 네트워크를 파괴하십시오.

en: Destroy the vertical take-off attack jets coming from the FARP.
ko: FARP에서 나오는 수직 이륙 공격 제트기를 파괴하십시오.

en: Land at any of the airbases or aircraft carrier.
Take on two enemy fighters with your wingman.
ko: 윙맨과 함께 두 명의 적 전투기를 상대하십시오.

en: Surprise! More fighters to kill. Where will they come from?
ko: 서프라이즈! 파괴할 적 전투기가 증원되었습니다. 그들은 어디에서 왔을까요?

en: Practice landing on the aircraft carrier.
A variety of hostile targets to destroy.  Practice using the aircraft as a fighter, a striker, or a mix of both.
ko: 파괴 할 다양한 적대적인 표적. 항공기를 전투기, 폭격기 또는 둘 다 사용하여 연습하십시오.

en: Destroy the enemy fire control radars around south city.
ko: 남쪽 도시 주변의 적 사격 통제 레이더를 파괴하십시오.

en: Destroy the naval group to the east.
Search for and destroy enemy fighters.
Refuel without landing. Fuel must be below 95% for the tanker to serve.
ko: 착륙하지 않고 급유하십시오. 유조선이 작동하려면 연료가 95 % 미만이어야합니다.

en: No enemies or objectives.  Just fly around and have fun!
ko: 적이나 임무가 없습니다. 그냥 날아 다니며 즐기세요!

en: Free flight in the twin-city bay map. No enemies or objectives.
ko: 트윈 시티 베이 지도에서 자유 비행. 적이나 목표가 없습니다.

en:
Various air and land targets are scattered around the area. Practice using your sensors and weapons to find and destroy the targets without worrying about them shooting back.

Several airbases and a carrier are available for you to use for rearming and refuelling if necessary.
ko:
다양한 공중 및 지상 표적이 지역 주변에 흩어져 있습니다. 센서와 무기를 사용하여 반격의 염려없이 목표물을 찾아 파괴하는 연습을하십시오.

 필요한 경우 재 무장 및 급유에 사용할 수있는 여러 공군 기지와 항모를 사용할 수 있습니다.

en: In this scenario, you will start in the air with a wingman.  Fly towards the island and take out the two enemy fighters.
ko: 이 시나리오에서는 윙맨과 함께 공중에서 시작합니다. 섬을 향해 날아가 두 명의 적 전투기를 제거하세요.

en: You will start in the air near the carrier.  Find it, then circle around for a landing approach.
ko: 항모 근처에서 비행을 시작합니다. 찾은 다음 착륙 접근을 위해 주위를 돌으십시오.

en:
Several enemy air, land, and naval units are scattered around the island.
Complete each of the mission objectives and return to the carrier.
ko: 여러 적의 공중, 지상, 해상 유닛이 섬 주변에 흩어져 있습니다. 각 임무 목표를 완료하고 항공 모함으로 돌아갑니다.

en: You may need to return to the carrier to refuel and rearm during the mission.
ko: 임무를 수행하는 동안 연료를 보급하고 재정비하려면 항모로 돌아 가야 할 수도 있습니다.

en: Practice aerial refueling with the F/A-26B.  Make sure to start off with a partially empty fuel tank.  Otherwise, the tanker will not lower to fuel boom.
ko: F / A-26B로 공중 급유를 연습하세요. 부분적으로 비어있는 연료 탱크로 시작하십시오. 그렇지 않으면 급유기가 연료 붐을 내리지 않습니다.

en: Just fly around and have fun!
Defend the city from the enemy attack.

An unidentified flying object has been detected over the island.  It appears to be giving off the same signals as those recorded near the recent attacks on mainland cities, so we're assuming hostility.  Find it and destroy it at all cost.
ko: 섬에서 미확인 비행 물체가 감지되었습니다. 최근 본토 도시에 대한 공격 근처에서 기록 된 신호와 동일한 신호를 발산하는 것으로 보이므로 적대기를 가정하고 있습니다. 그것을 찾아서 파괴하십시오.

en: A short campaign for the F/A-26B based around mountainous desert regions.
ko: 산악 사막 지역을 기반으로 한 F / A-26B의 짧은 캠페인입니다.

en: Defend the airbase supply depots from the incoming enemy attack.
ko: 들어오는 적의 공격으로부터 공군 기지 보급 창고를 방어하십시오.

en: Prevent the enemy from destroying all of the storage depots.
ko: 적군이 모든 창고를 파괴하는 것을 방지하십시오.

en: Destroy bomber (HB-106) and 2 escorts (ASF-30) before they destroy the depots.
ko: Destroy bomber (HB-106) and 2 escorts (ASF-30) before they destroy the depots.

en: Destroy 3 strikers (GAV-25), 2 escorts (ASF-30) before they destroy the depots.
ko: Destroy 3 strikers (GAV-25), 2 escorts (ASF-30) before they destroy the depots.

en: Destroy the artillery unit before it does more damage to the depots.
ko: Destroy the artillery unit before it does more damage to the depots.

en: Mission complete!  Land back at the airbase.
ko: 임무 완료! 공군 기지에 다시 착륙하십시오.

en: Destroy the 2 fighters (ASF-58) before they can take down our AWACs.
ko: Destroy the 2 fighters (ASF-58) before they can take down our AWACs.

en: Turn the tables and attack the enemy airbases' supplies.
ko: Turn the tables and attack the enemy airbases' supplies.

en: Destroy the enemy depots at the northern airbase.
ko: Destroy the enemy depots at the northern airbase.

en: Mission complete!  Land back at the airbase.
ko: 임무 완료! 공군 기지에 다시 착륙하십시오.

en: Destroy the enemy depots at the eastern airbase.
ko: Destroy the enemy depots at the eastern airbase.

en: Escort a strike group sent to destroy ships at the enemy's naval testing area.
ko: Escort a strike group sent to destroy ships at the enemy's naval testing area.

en: SEAD & protect X-Ray while they complete anti-shipping mission.
ko: SEAD & protect X-Ray while they complete anti-shipping mission.

en: Join the group of Anti-Ship strikers.
ko: Join the group of Anti-Ship strikers.

en: Protect the bomber while it attacks the remaining ships.
ko: Protect the bomber while it attacks the remaining ships.

en: Follow and protect the strike group along the way to the attack waypoint.
ko: Follow and protect the strike group along the way to the attack waypoint.

en: Destroy the fighters threatening X-Ray strike group.
ko: Destroy the fighters threatening X-Ray strike group.

en: Defend a tanker from airborne threats while it rendezvous with allied bombers.
ko: Defend a tanker from airborne threats while it rendezvous with allied bombers.

en: Defend the tanker as it rendezvous with bomber group Sierra.
ko: Defend the tanker as it rendezvous with bomber group Sierra.

en: Defend the tanker and bombers as they refuel and return to base.
ko: Defend the tanker and bombers as they refuel and return to base.

en: Our naval strike group will be departing from port on the western coast. Hostile forces are trying to stop them.
ko: Our naval strike group will be departing from port on the western coast. Hostile forces are trying to stop them.

en: Defend the carrier fleet as it embarks form the  port.
ko: Defend the carrier fleet as it embarks form the  port.

en: Destroy armored vehicles moving towards the base.
ko: Destroy armored vehicles moving towards the base.

en: Destroy ground targets moving through the canyons towards the base.
ko: Destroy ground targets moving through the canyons towards the base.

en: Destroy hostile bomber and its escorts.
ko: Destroy hostile bomber and its escorts.

en: Participate in a strike on hostile military targets.
ko: Participate in a strike on hostile military targets.

en: General objective: Fly Combat Air Patrol.
ko: General objective: Fly Combat Air Patrol.

en: Destroy air targets launching from enemy carrier.
ko: Destroy air targets launching from enemy carrier.

en: Shift CAP focus to the next waypoint.
ko: Shift CAP focus to the next waypoint.

en: Destroy aircraft departing from the enemy airbase.
ko: Destroy aircraft departing from the enemy airbase.

en: Destroy enemy bomber and escorts threatening carrier.
ko: Destroy enemy bomber and escorts threatening carrier.

en: Approach the attack waypoint with the other air groups.
ko: Approach the attack waypoint with the other air groups.

en: The carrier group's next target is one of the enemy's main sources of oil.
ko: The carrier group's next target is one of the enemy's main sources of oil.

en: Fly to objective waypoint and await further instructions.
ko: Fly to objective waypoint and await further instructions.

en: Find and destroy the high priority target.
ko: Find and destroy the high priority target.

en: End the conflict for good by launching a heavy strike on the command center.
ko: End the conflict for good by launching a heavy strike on the command center.

en: Follow the wing leader and her commands on the way to the AO.
ko: Follow the wing leader and her commands on the way to the AO.

en: Destroy all supply depots in the base.
ko: Destroy all supply depots in the base.

en: Disable any remaining air defenses around the base.
ko: Disable any remaining air defenses around the base.

en: Protect the transport and the team of soldiers it carries.
ko: Protect the transport and the team of soldiers it carries.

en: Take off and wait for wingmen.
ko: Take off and wait for wingmen.

en: Destroy tanks threatening the raid team.
ko: Destroy tanks threatening the raid team.

en:
You are stationed at our most remote airbase, closest to the enemy border.

The enemy seeks to destroy the airbase's supplies in order to prevent us from conducting airstrikes in this region.
ko:
You are stationed at our most remote airbase, closest to the enemy border.

The enemy seeks to destroy the airbase's supplies in order to prevent us from conducting airstrikes in this region.

en:
Intel has revealed that the enemy has launched a multi-pronged effort to attack the airbase.

A small group of hostile self-propelled artillery have mobilized to get into firing range of our supply depots.
ko:
Intel has revealed that the enemy has launched a multi-pronged effort to attack the airbase.

A small group of hostile self-propelled artillery have mobilized to get into firing range of our supply depots.

en:
While it will be necessary to destroy the artillery, we believe that the attack is aimed to distract us from a follow-up airstrike.

The type of attackers, their locations, and numbers are unknown at this time.
ko:
While it will be necessary to destroy the artillery, we believe that the attack is aimed to distract us from a follow-up airstrike.

The type of attackers, their locations, and numbers are unknown at this time.

en:
An E-4 AWACS will be deployed in order to aid in locating the airborne threats.

Due to our proximity to enemy territory, the AWACS will be vulnerable.  Please defend it if necessary.
ko:
An E-4 AWACS will be deployed in order to aid in locating the airborne threats.

Due to our proximity to enemy territory, the AWACS will be vulnerable.  Please defend it if necessary.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective:
Defend airbase supply depots.

Known targets:
3x self-propelled artillery

Unknown targets:
Bombers and/or attack aircraft.
ko:
SUMMARY:
Objective:
Defend airbase supply depots.

Known targets:
3x self-propelled artillery

Unknown targets:
Bombers and/or attack aircraft.

en:
Now's our chance to head back out and return the favor to the enemy.

They occupy two airbases -- one to the northeast, and one further due north.
ko:
Now's our chance to head back out and return the favor to the enemy.

They occupy two airbases -- one to the northeast, and one further due north.

en:
You must destroy the 4 supply depots at each base, for a total of 8 targets.

The enemy is most likely expecting us, so they probably beefed up air defenses as well as numerous aircraft on patrol.

Use the cover of darkness and terrain to mask your approach to the targets.
ko:
You must destroy the 4 supply depots at each base, for a total of 8 targets.

The enemy is most likely expecting us, so they probably beefed up air defenses as well as numerous aircraft on patrol.

Use the cover of darkness and terrain to mask your approach to the targets.

en:
We have gathered intel on the near exact locations of their supplies, which will be set as the objective waypoints.

How you want to attack is up to you.
I recommend to remain radar silent to avoid detection.
ko:
We have gathered intel on the near exact locations of their supplies, which will be set as the objective waypoints.

How you want to attack is up to you.
I recommend to remain radar silent to avoid detection.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective: 
- Destroy the 8 supply depots at each base (4 each).

Threats:
- Numerous radar and IR SAM sites
- Hostile combat air patrol
ko:
SUMMARY:
Objective: 
- Destroy the 8 supply depots at each base (4 each).

Threats:
- Numerous radar and IR SAM sites
- Hostile combat air patrol

en:
You've been transferred to the airbase near Gloom Lake.  

This lake lies on another border between our nation and the enemy's, and is where they conduct tests on naval vessels and aircraft.
ko:
You've been transferred to the airbase near Gloom Lake.  

This lake lies on another border between our nation and the enemy's, and is where they conduct tests on naval vessels and aircraft.

en:
There have been an unusually high number of enemy drones harassing us recently.  They fly dangerously close to our base and force us to take defensive measures.  

We believe that they're attempting to distract us while they test new military technologies.
ko:
There have been an unusually high number of enemy drones harassing us recently.  They fly dangerously close to our base and force us to take defensive measures.  

We believe that they're attempting to distract us while they test new military technologies.

en:
In order to put a damper on their research efforts, we're sending out a group of F/A-26Bs configured to sink their test ships.

Although this is a testing area, the enemy ships are fully functional and armed.
ko:
In order to put a damper on their research efforts, we're sending out a group of F/A-26Bs configured to sink their test ships.

Although this is a testing area, the enemy ships are fully functional and armed.

en:
You and your wingmen are tasked to destroy enemy air defenses and patrol aircraft, to allow the strikers to perform the anti-shipping attack.

The strikers will be in the air waiting for you.  Join them and escort them along their attack path.
ko:
You and your wingmen are tasked to destroy enemy air defenses and patrol aircraft, to allow the strikers to perform the anti-shipping attack.

The strikers will be in the air waiting for you.  Join them and escort them along their attack path.

en:
When you reach the end of the attack path, the strikers will begin anti-shipping. Target radars to prevent them from defending against the attack.

Simultaneously, allied combat air patrol will be vectored to the area to help keep enemy aircraft away.
ko:
When you reach the end of the attack path, the strikers will begin anti-shipping. Target radars to prevent them from defending against the attack.

Simultaneously, allied combat air patrol will be vectored to the area to help keep enemy aircraft away.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective: Support strikers while they attack enemy ships.
- Suppress enemy air defenses
- Defend strikers from enemy air patrols

Primary Targets:
- Radars
- Aggressive Aircraft

Threats:
- Ships
- Aircraft
- SAMs
- AAA
ko:
SUMMARY:
Objective: Support strikers while they attack enemy ships.
- Suppress enemy air defenses
- Defend strikers from enemy air patrols

Primary Targets:
- Radars
- Aggressive Aircraft

Threats:
- Ships
- Aircraft
- SAMs
- AAA

en:
A couple of bombers are returning from a long range mission.  Their fuel reserves are low, so we're sending out a KC-49 tanker to provide air-to-air refuelling.

We are concerned that enemy aircraft will intercept the tanker, which is where you and your wingmen come in.
ko:
A couple of bombers are returning from a long range mission.  Their fuel reserves are low, so we're sending out a KC-49 tanker to provide air-to-air refuelling.

We are concerned that enemy aircraft will intercept the tanker, which is where you and your wingmen come in.

en:
Fly with the tanker and keep it safe. Maintain active radar and RWR so you are aware of hostiles. 

AWACs will also be available to help spot incoming threats.
ko:
Fly with the tanker and keep it safe. Maintain active radar and RWR so you are aware of hostiles. 

AWACs will also be available to help spot incoming threats.

en:
SUMMARY
Objective: 
- Escort the tanker to the rendezvous.  
- Engage all hostile aircraft that approach.
- Mission complete when the tanker and bombers return to base.

Threats:
- Hostile aircraft
ko:
SUMMARY
Objective: 
- Escort the tanker to the rendezvous.  
- Engage all hostile aircraft that approach.
- Mission complete when the tanker and bombers return to base.

Threats:
- Hostile aircraft

en:
It's time to send a naval strike group deep into enemy territory.  The aircraft carrier and its escorts will soon be ready to depart, but enemy forces are close.  

They will likely attempt to stop the carrier group before our mission can even begin.
ko:
It's time to send a naval strike group deep into enemy territory.  The aircraft carrier and its escorts will soon be ready to depart, but enemy forces are close.  

They will likely attempt to stop the carrier group before our mission can even begin.

en:
Your job is to protect the ships, onboard aircraft, and the naval base from the enemy attack.  Hostile aircraft and land vehicles are approaching.  

Once the coast is clear, you will land on the carrier and join on the offensive.
ko:
Your job is to protect the ships, onboard aircraft, and the naval base from the enemy attack.  Hostile aircraft and land vehicles are approaching.  

Once the coast is clear, you will land on the carrier and join on the offensive.

en:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Defend naval strike group and naval base

Threats:
- Fighter Aircraft
- Bombers
- Tanks
- Mobile Anti-Air
ko:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Defend naval strike group and naval base

Threats:
- Fighter Aircraft
- Bombers
- Tanks
- Mobile Anti-Air

en:
The carrier group's first stop is a small northern island territory occupied by the enemy.

They have a few military bases here and use the island to stage their attacks on our western coast.
ko:
The carrier group's first stop is a small northern island territory occupied by the enemy.

They have a few military bases here and use the island to stage their attacks on our western coast.

en:
The island is a valuable asset to the enemy's air and naval forces, so it's our duty to halt their operations here.

We will launch a full on air assault.
ko:
The island is a valuable asset to the enemy's air and naval forces, so it's our duty to halt their operations here.

We will launch a full on air assault.

en:
There are 4 major components to the attack, which will be split up among 4 specialized air groups.

Whiskey group will suppress enemy air defenses. X-ray group will attack ground targets such as armored vehicles and supply depots.  Bravo will sink the enemy ships.
ko:
There are 4 major components to the attack, which will be split up among 4 specialized air groups.

Whiskey group will suppress enemy air defenses. X-ray group will attack ground targets such as armored vehicles and supply depots.  Bravo will sink the enemy ships.

en:
Kilo group, your group, will fly combat air patrol and keep the enemy fighters away from the other groups.

The enemy only has a few groups of fighters in the air, but they have a carrier full of aircraft ready to go, and an airbase not far from our point of entry.
ko:
Kilo group, your group, will fly combat air patrol and keep the enemy fighters away from the other groups.

The enemy only has a few groups of fighters in the air, but they have a carrier full of aircraft ready to go, and an airbase not far from our point of entry.

en: All groups will maintain open communications, but you will only have command over your own group.  Focus on your own objective (CAP) but maintain awareness of the bigger picture.
ko: All groups will maintain open communications, but you will only have command over your own group.  Focus on your own objective (CAP) but maintain awareness of the bigger picture.

en:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Combat air patrol

Targets:
- Multiple hostile aircraft

Threats:
- Hostile Aircraft
- SAMs
- Ships
ko:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Combat air patrol

Targets:
- Multiple hostile aircraft

Threats:
- Hostile Aircraft
- SAMs
- Ships

en:
We have located the enemy's main source of oil off the shore of some remote islands.  

The carrier group has been sent to destroy the oil platforms and further reduce the enemy's ability to fuel war.
ko:
We have located the enemy's main source of oil off the shore of some remote islands.  

The carrier group has been sent to destroy the oil platforms and further reduce the enemy's ability to fuel war.

en:
There seems to be an unusually high naval military presence here, so the guided missile cruisers will be assisting your attack.

Air groups X-ray and Sierra will be primarily focused on SEAD, while Bravo will provide CAP.
ko:
There seems to be an unusually high naval military presence here, so the guided missile cruisers will be assisting your attack.

Air groups X-ray and Sierra will be primarily focused on SEAD, while Bravo will provide CAP.

en:
Your group, Kilo, will be responsible for striking the oil platforms.

We need the platforms to be destroyed beyond all repair, so you can either destroy all key components on the platform, or destroy two support pillars to topple the entire platform.
ko:
Your group, Kilo, will be responsible for striking the oil platforms.

We need the platforms to be destroyed beyond all repair, so you can either destroy all key components on the platform, or destroy two support pillars to topple the entire platform.

en:
Our cruisers will approach from the north, on the western side of the ridge. 

The air groups will approach on the eastern side of the ridge at low altitude. You should remain undetected until you reach the channel.
ko:
Our cruisers will approach from the north, on the western side of the ridge. 

The air groups will approach on the eastern side of the ridge at low altitude. You should remain undetected until you reach the channel.

en:
The SEAD attack from the east should occur at the same time that the cruiser anti-ship missiles reach the enemy.

This will keep their defenses saturated while Kilo comes in to take down the oil platforms.
ko:
The SEAD attack from the east should occur at the same time that the cruiser anti-ship missiles reach the enemy.

This will keep their defenses saturated while Kilo comes in to take down the oil platforms.

en: There may be other ground targets for you, but we will keep you updated on those as we acquire more information.
ko: There may be other ground targets for you, but we will keep you updated on those as we acquire more information.

en:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Destroy 4 oil platforms

Threats
- Ships
- SAMs
- Aircraft
ko:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Destroy 4 oil platforms

Threats
- Ships
- SAMs
- Aircraft

en:
This mission will have two phases.
On the first phase, Kilo 1-1 will lead the flight into enemy territory.

You will be Kilo 1-2, and are assigned to support the flight lead.  Execute her commands to destroy secondary targets on the way to the enemy base.
ko:
This mission will have two phases.
On the first phase, Kilo 1-1 will lead the flight into enemy territory.

You will be Kilo 1-2, and are assigned to support the flight lead.  Execute her commands to destroy secondary targets on the way to the enemy base.

en:
The mission is scheduled to start when one of the enemy's coastal defense sites goes down temporarily.

We expect the defenses to resume operation when they spot your approach, but at least it will give you an opportunity to disable them before they can acquire you.
ko:
The mission is scheduled to start when one of the enemy's coastal defense sites goes down temporarily.

We expect the defenses to resume operation when they spot your approach, but at least it will give you an opportunity to disable them before they can acquire you.

en:
The flight path will be low, weaving through the valleys to avoid line of sight with enemy radar.

Maintain formation with Kilo 1 for the entirety of the ingress phase.
ko:
The flight path will be low, weaving through the valleys to avoid line of sight with enemy radar.

Maintain formation with Kilo 1 for the entirety of the ingress phase.

en:
The secondary targets are coastal defenses at Alpha and two IR SAM units at Bravo. Destroying them will help clear the way for the bomber. 

Again, flight leader Kilo 1-1 will call the shots on these targets.
ko:
The secondary targets are coastal defenses at Alpha and two IR SAM units at Bravo. Destroying them will help clear the way for the bomber. 

Again, flight leader Kilo 1-1 will call the shots on these targets.

en:
The primary objective will begin when you reach the base at Charlie.

Allied rocket artillery will be in the area launching strikes on the base's air defenses.
ko:
The primary objective will begin when you reach the base at Charlie.

Allied rocket artillery will be in the area launching strikes on the base's air defenses.

en:
The primary targets are rows of cylindrical tents lined up from east to west.

Your flight path will allow you to strike multiple targets in a single low-altitude bombing pass.
ko:
The primary targets are rows of cylindrical tents lined up from east to west.

Your flight path will allow you to strike multiple targets in a single low-altitude bombing pass.

en: After the first pass, flight lead duties will be passed over to you (Kilo 1-2).  Lead your wingmen to take down the remaining targets.
ko: After the first pass, flight lead duties will be passed over to you (Kilo 1-2).  Lead your wingmen to take down the remaining targets.

en:
A group of F-45A's will take off from a nearby FARP to help keep enemy aircraft and other threats off of you and your wingmen.

Once primary targets have been destroyed, an AV-42C will also dispatch from here to deliver troops to the headquarters and capture the enemy leaders.
ko:
A group of F-45A's will take off from a nearby FARP to help keep enemy aircraft and other threats off of you and your wingmen.

Once primary targets have been destroyed, an AV-42C will also dispatch from here to deliver troops to the headquarters and capture the enemy leaders.

en:
You will be tasked to protect them at that time, but we'll update you on that final operation when we get to it.

Focus on supporting your wingmen during the flight through hostile territory and destroying the primary targets.
ko:
You will be tasked to protect them at that time, but we'll update you on that final operation when we get to it.

Focus on supporting your wingmen during the flight through hostile territory and destroying the primary targets.

en:
SUMMARY

OBJECTIVES
-  Clear air defenses for bombers
- *Destroy enemy assets
-  Protect troop transport

THREATS
- IR and Radar SAMs
- Aircraft
ko:
SUMMARY

OBJECTIVES
-  Clear air defenses for bombers
- *Destroy enemy assets
-  Protect troop transport

THREATS
- IR and Radar SAMs
- Aircraft

en: A small collection of quick missions for the F-45A.
ko: A small collection of quick missions for the F-45A.

en: Take the lead on this two-part mission to take down hostile bombers.
ko: Take the lead on this two-part mission to take down hostile bombers.

en: Destroy the long range MAD-4 Radar (M4) near the airbase.
ko: Destroy the long range MAD-4 Radar (M4) near the airbase.

en: Destroy the fighters taking off from the base with the help of India group.
ko: Destroy the fighters taking off from the base with the help of India group.

en: Destroy bombers taking off from second airbase.
ko: Destroy bombers taking off from second airbase.

en: Attack high value targets in an attack on enemy territory.
ko: Attack high value targets in an attack on enemy territory.

en: Locate and destroy the command & control bunkers
ko: Locate and destroy the command & control bunkers

en: Destroy the artillery attacking our ships.
ko: Destroy the artillery attacking our ships.

en: Find and destroy the highly capable enemy stealth fighters.
ko: Find and destroy the highly capable enemy stealth fighters.

en: Find and destroy the enemy bomber aircraft.
ko: Find and destroy the enemy bomber aircraft.

en: Do not let the enemy destroy either of our carriers!
ko: Do not let the enemy destroy either of our carriers!

en: Practice arrested or vertical landings on a moving carrier.
ko: Practice arrested or vertical landings on a moving carrier.

en: Search for and destroy enemy weapon caches. Avoid detection or pay the price. Once they know where you are, they'll do anything to stop you.
ko: Search for and destroy enemy weapon caches. Avoid detection or pay the price. Once they know where you are, they'll do anything to stop you.

en: Find and destroy enemy weapon caches. Locations unknown.
ko: Find and destroy enemy weapon caches. Locations unknown.

en: Return to and land on the helipad.
ko: Return to and land on the helipad.

en:
You will be the first to launch from the carrier.

Destroy the long range air defenses at the enemy coastal airbase Alpha first so that we can launch fighters.
ko:
You will be the first to launch from the carrier.

Destroy the long range air defenses at the enemy coastal airbase Alpha first so that we can launch fighters.

en: Once the air defenses are destroyed, CAP group India will launch from the carrier to help you clean up the enemy fighters.
ko: Once the air defenses are destroyed, CAP group India will launch from the carrier to help you clean up the enemy fighters.

en:
After clearing the fighters, land at the FARP to reconfigure for a purely air-to-air role. You will be joined by another F-45 to take down the enemy bombers taking off from airbase Bravo.

SEAD group Romeo will launch from the carrier to disable the SAM sites at Bravo.
ko:
After clearing the fighters, land at the FARP to reconfigure for a purely air-to-air role. You will be joined by another F-45 to take down the enemy bombers taking off from airbase Bravo.

SEAD group Romeo will launch from the carrier to disable the SAM sites at Bravo.

en: Destroy the two bombers from Bravo then return to carrier to complete the mission!
ko: Destroy the two bombers from Bravo then return to carrier to complete the mission!

en:
Complete all of the objectives, then return to the assault carrier.

You can complete them in any order you choose.

There's a mix of hardened surface targets and air targets.
ko:
Complete all of the objectives, then return to the assault carrier.

You can complete them in any order you choose.

There's a mix of hardened surface targets and air targets.

en:
Enemy rocket artillery have moved into range and have begun firing on our fleet from the other side of a mountain.

They have a low hit probability, but we must destroy them.
ko:
Enemy rocket artillery have moved into range and have begun firing on our fleet from the other side of a mountain.

They have a low hit probability, but we must destroy them.

en: Enemy bombers have also been known to operate from this area. If they decide to deploy them against our assault fleet, they will be a high priority target.
ko: Enemy bombers have also been known to operate from this area. If they decide to deploy them against our assault fleet, they will be a high priority target.

en: We have little intel on their whereabouts, but a handful of enemy stealth fighters are stationed by the bay and must be destroyed.
ko: We have little intel on their whereabouts, but a handful of enemy stealth fighters are stationed by the bay and must be destroyed.

en: Finally, you must find the enemy command post and destroy the two bunkers. The bunkers will likely be adjacent to large supply tents.
ko: Finally, you must find the enemy command post and destroy the two bunkers. The bunkers will likely be adjacent to large supply tents.

en: Enemy bases are well defended, so use caution when operating near them.
ko: Enemy bases are well defended, so use caution when operating near them.

en: The mission will be considered a failure if either of our carriers are destroyed.
ko: The mission will be considered a failure if either of our carriers are destroyed.

en:
No objectives or enemies.

You will start at 300kts, 1000ft above two carriers.  Contact one of them to request clearance to land.
ko:
No objectives or enemies.

You will start at 300kts, 1000ft above two carriers.  Contact one of them to request clearance to land.

en: You are stationed at small FARP (forward arming and refueling point) near an enemy airbase.  Unfortunately, you only have enough supplies for one last sortie, and it's a tough one.
ko: You are stationed at small FARP (forward arming and refueling point) near an enemy airbase.  Unfortunately, you only have enough supplies for one last sortie, and it's a tough one.

en: The mission is to destroy 3 enemy weapon caches.  We don't know exactly where they are, but they are most likely near air defenses.  Based on their radar emissions, we have estimated the positions of 4 sites.  The caches may all be at one site, or spread out between them.
ko: The mission is to destroy 3 enemy weapon caches.  We don't know exactly where they are, but they are most likely near air defenses.  Based on their radar emissions, we have estimated the positions of 4 sites.  The caches may all be at one site, or spread out between them.

en: You don't have any support on this mission.  No extra fuel, no rearming, no wingmen, nothing.  With scattered SAM sites and numerous enemy air patrols, the odds are stacked against you.  Use stealthy tactics to maneuver around the area and destroy the targets.
ko: You don't have any support on this mission.  No extra fuel, no rearming, no wingmen, nothing.  With scattered SAM sites and numerous enemy air patrols, the odds are stacked against you.  Use stealthy tactics to maneuver around the area and destroy the targets.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective:
  - Destroy the 3 weapon caches (supply tents)

Threats:
  - SAMs
  - Patrolling aircraft
ko:
SUMMARY:
Objective:
  - Destroy the 3 weapon caches (supply tents)

Threats:
  - SAMs
  - Patrolling aircraft

en: Learn how to use the cannon, rockets, and targeting system.
ko: 기관포, 로켓 및 조준 시스템 사용 방법을 배워봅시다.

en: Learn how to use the hover autopilot feature.
ko: 호버링 자동 조종 기능을 사용하는 방법을 배워 봅시다.

en:
Today we will be learning how to operate the AV-42C.

The start-up procedure is not very complicated, so let's jump in and get started.
ko:
오늘은 AV-42C 작동 방법을 배우겠습니다.

시동 절차는 그다지 복잡하지 않으므로 바로 시작해 보겠습니다.

en: The AV-42C is capable of equipping various weapons.  Today you will learn how to use the 30mm GAU-8 cannon, and the Hydra-70 unguided rockets.  You will also learn how to find and acquire targets using the TGP.
ko: AV-42C는 다양한 무기를 장착 할 수 있습니다. 오늘은 30mm GAU-8 대포와 Hydra-70 무유도 로켓 사용법을 배웁니다. 또한 TGP를 사용하여 대상을 찾고 추적하는 방법도 배웁니다.

en: Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the hover autopilot, you can take off, hover, and land with ease.
ko: 수직 비행은 까다로울 수 있지만 호버링 자동 조종 기능을 사용하면 쉽게 이륙, 호버링 및 착륙 할 수 있습니다.

en: Learn how to use air-to-ground missiles.
Destroy some of the targets around the waypoint using the AGM-114.
ko: AGM-114를 사용하여 웨이 포인트 주변의 일부 목표물을 파괴하십시오.

en: Learn how to use the cannon, rockets, and targeting system.
ko: 기관포, 로켓 및 조준 시스템 사용 방법을 배워봅시다.

en: Learn how to use the hover autopilot feature.
ko: 호버링 자동 조종 기능을 사용하는 방법을 배워 봅시다.

en: Today, you will learn how to use air-to-ground missiles (AGMs) to destroy armored ground targets.
ko: 오늘은 공대지 미사일 (AGM)을 사용하여 장갑 지상 목표물을 파괴하는 방법을 배웁니다.

en: Learn how to use the virtual flight controls to taxi, take off, and land the AV-42C "Kestrel".
ko: 가상 비행 컨트롤을 사용하여 AV-42C "Kestrel"을 택시, 이착륙하는 방법을 알아보십시오.

en:
Today we will be learning how to operate the AV-42C.

The start-up procedure is not very complicated, so let's jump in and get started.
ko:
오늘은 AV-42C 작동 방법을 배우겠습니다.

시동 절차는 그다지 복잡하지 않으므로 바로 시작해 보겠습니다.

en: The AV-42C is capable of equipping various weapons.  Today you will learn how to use the 30mm GAU-8 cannon, and the Hydra-70 unguided rockets.  You will also learn how to find and acquire targets using the TGP.
ko: AV-42C는 다양한 무기를 장착 할 수 있습니다. 오늘은 30mm GAU-8 대포와 Hydra-70 무유도 로켓 사용법을 배웁니다. 또한 TGP를 사용하여 대상을 찾고 추적하는 방법도 배웁니다.

en: Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the hover autopilot, you can take off, hover, and land with ease.
ko: 수직 비행은 까다로울 수 있지만 호버링 자동 조종 기능을 사용하면 쉽게 이륙, 호버링 및 착륙 할 수 있습니다.

en: Learn how to use the radar to find, track, and lock onto aircraft.
ko: 레이더를 사용하여 항공기를 찾고, 추적하고, 락온하는 방법을 알아 봅니다.

en: Shoot the target with an AIM-120
Learn how to use the ARAD and AGM-88 to destroy radar targets.
ko: ARAD 및 AGM-88을 사용하여 레이더 표적을 파괴하는 방법을 알아보십시오.

en: The F/A-26B is equipped with powerful forward facing radar. Learn how to use it to detect and track other aircraft.  Lock onto enemy targets to allow you to fire radar guided missiles.
ko: F / A-26B에는 강력한 전방 레이더가 장착되어 있습니다. 다른 항공기를 감지하고 추적하는 데 사용하는 방법을 알아 봅니다. 레이더 유도 미사일을 발사 할 수 있도록 적 표적에 고정하세요.

en:
One of the most abundant and dangerous threats to aircraft are Surface-to-Air Missiles (SAMs), most of which rely on radar to find and track targets.

Suppression of Enemy Air Defense (SEAD) operations neutralize or destroy these threats.
ko:
One of the most abundant and dangerous threats to aircraft are Surface-to-Air Missiles (SAMs), most of which rely on radar to find and track targets.

Suppression of Enemy Air Defense (SEAD) operations neutralize or destroy these threats.

en:
One method of performing SEAD involves destroying the radar used by the SAMs.

You will learn how to use the Anti-Radar Attack Display (ARAD) in conjunction with the AGM-88 weapon to locate, target, and destroy enemy radars.
ko:
One method of performing SEAD involves destroying the radar used by the SAMs.

You will learn how to use the Anti-Radar Attack Display (ARAD) in conjunction with the AGM-88 weapon to locate, target, and destroy enemy radars.

en: Pick up the soldiers at the waypoint.
Transport the soldiers to the objective waypoint.
Destroy the enemy units on the road towards our soldiers.
Destroy the units in the city by the landing zone.
Strike enemy artillery. This mission is intended to test the performance of a large custom map.
ko: 적의 포병을 공격하십시오. 이 임무는 대형 사용자 지정 맵 로딩 성능을 테스트하기 위한 것입니다.

en: Form up with your air group and fly the patrol path, MSN-1
ko: 항공 그룹을 구성하고 순찰 경로 MSN-1을 비행하십시오.

en: Welcome to the air-to-ground missile tutorial!
ko: 공대지 미사일 튜토리얼에 오신 것을 환영합니다!

en: Air-to-ground missiles (AGM) are useful for precisely hitting light to medium armored ground targets
ko: 공대지 미사일 (AGM)은 경 장갑 지상 목표물을 정확하게 타격하는 데 유용합니다.

en: You will use the TGP to designate targets for the AGMs
These are small, laser-guided, anti-tank missiles
Since they home in on the laser point emitted by your TGP, you must maintain line of sight to the target until it hits
ko: 그들은 당신의 TGP에서 방출되는 레이저를 따라 유도 되기 때문에, 당신은 목표물에 도달 할 때까지 시야를 유지해야합니다

en: To fire it, designate a target using the TGP, point your aircraft at the target until the missile locks on, then pull the trigger to fire
ko: 발사하려면 TGP를 사용하여 표적을 지정하고 미사일이 잠길 때까지 항공기를 표적에 겨냥한 다음 방아쇠를 당겨 발사하십시오.

en: You can also switch the missile seeker's uncage mode to MANUAL, which will allow you to fire at targets off boresight
ko: 또한 미사일 시커의 케이지 해제 모드를 MANUAL로 전환하여 시야각을 벗어난 목표물을 향해 발사 할 수 있습니다.

en: In MANUAL mode, you hold the trigger to uncage the seeker, then press the weapon switch button to fire
ko: 수동 모드에서 방아쇠를 눌러 시커를 풀고 무기 스위치 버튼을 눌러 발사합니다.

en: Try shooting the targets around the mission waypoint using the AGM-114
ko: AGM-114를 사용하여 미션 웨이 포인트 주변의 목표물을 쏴보십시오

en: Remember, you need to maintain line of sight with your TGP in order to guide the missile to the target
ko: 미사일을 목표물로 유도하려면 TGP로 시선을 유지해야합니다.

en: Great! Now switch to the AGM-65
This is a larger, slightly heavier hitting anti-tank missile with a more advanced optical seeker
ko: This is a larger, slightly heavier hitting anti-tank missile with a more advanced optical seeker

en: With this type of missile, you do not need to maintain a lock on the target after you fire at it
ko: With this type of missile, you do not need to maintain a lock on the target after you fire at it

en: The fire-and-forget capability allows you to fire at multiple targets in one pass, or take cover after firing
ko: The fire-and-forget capability allows you to fire at multiple targets in one pass, or take cover after firing

en: Try taking down the targets at the next waypoint and practice taking advantage of the fire-and-forget capability
ko: Try taking down the targets at the next waypoint and practice taking advantage of the fire-and-forget capability

en: Nice shooting!  This concludes the air-to-ground missile tutorial
ko: Nice shooting!  This concludes the air-to-ground missile tutorial

en: Welcome to the Radar tutorial for the F/A-26
ko: Welcome to the Radar tutorial for the F/A-26

en: Today, you will learn how to use the radar to find and track other aircraft, as well as designate targets for air to air missiles
ko: Today, you will learn how to use the radar to find and track other aircraft, as well as designate targets for air to air missiles

en: The display shows you a compressed representation of the radar's 120 degree field of view
ko: The display shows you a compressed representation of the radar's 120 degree field of view

en: The displayed range can be adjusted using the R+ and R- buttons
ko: The displayed range can be adjusted using the R+ and R- buttons

en: Press R+ repeatedly until the display is at max range
ko: Press R+ repeatedly until the display is at max range

en: As the radar sweeps over other aircraft, they will be displayed as blue icons for friends and orange icons for foes
ko: As the radar sweeps over other aircraft, they will be displayed as blue icons for friends and orange icons for foes

en: The left/right SCAN ANGLE can also be adjusted to allow the radar to scan more rapidly but in a smaller slice of the sky
ko: The left/right SCAN ANGLE can also be adjusted to allow the radar to scan more rapidly but in a smaller slice of the sky

en: Now, you can slew the target designator using the joystick's thumb control
ko: Now, you can slew the target designator using the joystick's thumb control

en: Slew the designator over a contact, and press in on the center of the thumb control to start tracking it
ko: Slew the designator over a contact, and press in on the center of the thumb control to start tracking it

en: You can track up to 4 contacts while still being able to scan the rest of the sky
ko: You can track up to 4 contacts while still being able to scan the rest of the sky

en: They will appear as small circle on your HUD, along with their corresponding number
ko: They will appear as small circle on your HUD, along with their corresponding number

en: In order to lock a target for weapons, click on a track again using the designator, or press the numbered MFD button on the left
ko: In order to lock a target for weapons, click on a track again using the designator, or press the numbered MFD button on the left

en: While a target is locked, the other tracks will continue to be displayed, but the radar will not be able to scan for new targets
ko: While a target is locked, the other tracks will continue to be displayed, but the radar will not be able to scan for new targets

en: Information about the locked target's bearing, range, altitude, airspeed, and aircraft type will appear on the bottom right of the display
ko: Information about the locked target's bearing, range, altitude, airspeed, and aircraft type will appear on the bottom right of the display

en: Use the UNLCK button to unlock the target, and the CLR button to clear the tracks
ko: Use the UNLCK button to unlock the target, and the CLR button to clear the tracks

en: For close in engagements, the radar can be switched to boresight mode using the MODE button
ko: For close in engagements, the radar can be switched to boresight mode using the MODE button

en: In this mode, the radar will point straight forward and lock onto the first contact it sees
ko: In this mode, the radar will point straight forward and lock onto the first contact it sees

en: If the radar is SOI, you can press the joystick thumb control to quickly unlock and find a new target
ko: If the radar is SOI, you can press the joystick thumb control to quickly unlock and find a new target

en: Now for some weapons practice. Go back to scan mode and find, track, and lock the enemy aircraft.
ko: Now for some weapons practice. Go back to scan mode and find, track, and lock the enemy aircraft.

en: Good. Now arm your weapon system and switch to the AIM-120
ko: Good. Now arm your weapon system and switch to the AIM-120

en: On the HUD, the locked target will appear as a small square.  The small dot is the shot lead cue
ko: On the HUD, the locked target will appear as a small square.  The small dot is the shot lead cue

en: When firing air to air missiles, aim for the lead cue to help the missile conserve energy as it steers toward the target
ko: When firing air to air missiles, aim for the lead cue to help the missile conserve energy as it steers toward the target

en: The DLZ is displayed on the right side of the HUD. The missile should be fired when the target chevron lies between the min and max marks
ko: The DLZ is displayed on the right side of the HUD. The missile should be fired when the target chevron lies between the min and max marks

en: By tracking multiple contacts, you can fire up to 4 AIM-120s on separate targets as long as you maintain line of sight with each of them
ko: By tracking multiple contacts, you can fire up to 4 AIM-120s on separate targets as long as you maintain line of sight with each of them

en: When the AIM-120's time to impact counter displays the letter M, it has switched to active homing and you no longer need to track it.
ko: When the AIM-120's time to impact counter displays the letter M, it has switched to active homing and you no longer need to track it.

en: Now, try shooting down the rest of the enemy air targets.
ko: Now, try shooting down the rest of the enemy air targets.

en: Out of missiles!  You hit some of the targets though!
ko: Out of missiles!  You hit some of the targets though!

en: Out of missiles!  You didn't hit anything.  Want to try again?
ko: Out of missiles!  You didn't hit anything.  Want to try again?

en: SEAD stands for Suppression of Enemy Air Defenses
ko: SEAD stands for Suppression of Enemy Air Defenses

en: You will use a combination of radar detecting sensors and special weapons to disable SAM sites
ko: You will use a combination of radar detecting sensors and special weapons to disable SAM sites

en: When a radar is searching for aircraft, it emits a signal that can be detected by your RWR
ko: When a radar is searching for aircraft, it emits a signal that can be detected by your RWR

en: The radar type, bearing, and approximate range is shown on the RWR display, relative to your position in the center
ko: The radar type, bearing, and approximate range is shown on the RWR display, relative to your position in the center

en: This display shows the same information gathered by the RWR, but allows you to select targets for ARMs
ko: This display shows the same information gathered by the RWR, but allows you to select targets for ARMs

en: You can also set radar sources to be displayed as diamonds in the HUD
ko: You can also set radar sources to be displayed as diamonds in the HUD

en: When you lower the AR visor, you'll be able to see all of the targets around you for better situational awareness
ko: When you lower the AR visor, you'll be able to see all of the targets around you for better situational awareness

en: Now you can use your joystick thumb control to slew the targeting cursor
ko: Now you can use your joystick thumb control to slew the targeting cursor

en: Slew the cursor onto the enemy radar, then press in on the thumb control to set the target
ko: Slew the cursor onto the enemy radar, then press in on the thumb control to set the target

en: A square will appear on the selected target in both the MFD and the HUD
ko: A square will appear on the selected target in both the MFD and the HUD

en: This is a high speed, fire-and-forget anti-radiation missile (ARM)
ko: This is a high speed, fire-and-forget anti-radiation missile (ARM)

en: When fired, it will home in on the radar source designated in the ARAD
ko: When fired, it will home in on the radar source designated in the ARAD

en: Once you have a target selected, all you need to do is fly toward the target, and fire once the missile is in range
ko: Once you have a target selected, all you need to do is fly toward the target, and fire once the missile is in range

en: Try taking out the SAM radars using the AGM-88
ko: Try taking out the SAM radars using the AGM-88

en: Great!  This is the end of the SEAD tutorial.
ko: Great!  This is the end of the SEAD tutorial.
